<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1730" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1730">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.124/17.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President asks that the Department recommend to serve under Doctor
                            Converse an engineer who has specialized in public water supply and
                            sewerage construction and has had responsible Chargé of such work. He is
                            wanted to supervise the design and construction of works at Iquitos.
                            Preferably member of American Society of Civil Engineers; must be
                            scrupulously honest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Howard.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>